description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a motivated and passionate nurse who is experienced in working in an innovative, fast-paced area or keen to develop this skill in a Haematology and Oncology Outpatient setting? &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If so we’d love to hear from you. We have an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic nurse who is ready for a Senior Staff nurse role in our committed, positive and supportive team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some experience in management would be useful or maybe you would like to take a new post in a new speciality. You will need to be innovative, organised, have time management and a zest for challenges, in a developing service to our patients. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Within our areas we care for and deliver treatment to patients with solid tumours and haematological disorders, through all stages of the cancer journey. We have an expanding service where staff can develop and flourish, while enjoying a positive work-life balance. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Caring for patients with cancer can be tough. Our supportive team-working culture will empower you to build up professional relationships with your patients and their family as you follow closely their progress. Our patients appreciate dealing with a familiar, reassuring face, with an in-depth knowledge of their individual situation and needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Can you see yourself in this role?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Experience with haematology and oncology would be a real bonus, but most important are true compassion and eagerness to learn.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be expected to work Monday to Friday 0800 to 18.00 in the Haematology and Oncology department, including some Bank Holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rizza Elaydo – Department Sister&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0117 342 27861&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rizza.elaydo@uhbw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
